All samples

Most 500 variable genes

data <- data$cpm[,rownames(salmon@phenoData)]
data <- log(data + 1)
xvar <- apply(log(data), 1, var)
genes500 <- head(sort(xvar, decreasing = TRUE), n = 500)
x500 <- log2(data[rownames(data) %in% names(genes500), ])

Heatmap

pCol <- salmon@phenoData[,1,drop = FALSE]
# pCol$Cage.ID <- as.factor(pCol$Cage.ID)
pheatmap(x500, scale = "row", show_rownames = F, col = viridis(50), show_colnames = F, annotation_col = pCol, main = "Clustering of samples based on top 500 variable genes")

Correlation

Computation

cor.mat <- cor(data)

Plot

corrplot(cor.mat,
  method = "color", type = "upper", title = "Correlation plot of samples",
  tl.cex = 0.9
)

PCA Tools

p <- pca(data, metadata = pCol, removeVar = 0.1)
## -- removing the lower 10% of variables based on variance
pscree <- screeplot(p,
  components = getComponents(p, 1:20),
  hline = 80, vline = 2.6, axisLabSize = 20, returnPlot = FALSE
) +
  geom_text(aes(4, 80, label = "80% explained variation", vjust = -1, size = 30))

ppairs <- pairsplot(p,
  components = getComponents(p, c(1:3)),
  triangle = TRUE, trianglelabSize = 12,
  hline = 0, vline = 0,
  pointSize = 0.8, gridlines.major = FALSE, gridlines.minor = FALSE,
  colby = "Group",
  title = "", titleLabSize = 16, plotaxes = FALSE,
  margingaps = unit(c(0.01, 0.01, 0.01, 0.01), "cm"),
  returnPlot = FALSE
)
## Coordinate system already present. Adding new coordinate system, which will replace the existing one.

## Coordinate system already present. Adding new coordinate system, which will replace the existing one.
## Coordinate system already present. Adding new coordinate system, which will replace the existing one.
## Coordinate system already present. Adding new coordinate system, which will replace the existing one.
pbiplot <- biplot(p,
  lab = FALSE,
  colby = "Group",
  hline = 0, vline = c(-25, 0, 25), vlineType = c("dotdash", "solid", "dashed"),
  gridlines.major = FALSE, gridlines.minor = FALSE,
  pointSize = 4, axisLabSize = 22,
  legendPosition = "left", legendLabSize = 18, legendIconSize = 6.0,
  drawConnectors = FALSE,
  title = "PCA bi-plot", subtitle = "PC1 versus PC2",
  caption = "2 PCs > 75%",
  returnPlot = FALSE, titleLabSize = 22, subtitleLabSize = 20
)

ploadings <- plotloadings(p,
  rangeRetain = 0.01, labSize = 5,
  title = "Loadings plot", axisLabSize = 20,
  subtitle = "PC1, PC2, PC3, PC4, PC5",
  caption = "Top 1% variables",
  shape = 23, shapeSizeRange = c(4, 4),
  col = c("limegreen", "black", "red3"),
  legendPosition = "none",
  drawConnectors = FALSE,
  returnPlot = FALSE
)
## -- variables retained:
## n-R5s100, RP23-402O17.1, Rpl15-ps3, RP23-8J15.3, RP23-8J15.7, Dcn, H3f3c, St6galnac4, RP23-3K10.3, Gm6741
top_row <- plot_grid(pscree, ppairs, pbiplot,
  ncol = 3,
  labels = c("A", "B  Pairs plot", "C"),
  label_fontfamily = "serif",
  label_fontface = "bold",
  label_size = 22,
  align = "h",
  rel_widths = c(1.05, 0.9, 1.05)
)

bottom_row <- plot_grid(ploadings,
  ncol = 1,
  labels = c("D"),
  label_fontfamily = "serif",
  label_fontface = "bold",
  label_size = 22,
  align = "h",
  rel_widths = c(1.5, 1.5)
)
plot_grid(top_row, bottom_row, ncol = 1, rel_heights = c(1.0, 1.0))

top_row <- plot_grid(pscree, pbiplot,
  ncol = 2,
  labels = c("A", "B"),
  label_fontfamily = "serif",
  label_fontface = "bold",
  label_size = 22,
  align = "h",
  rel_widths = c(1, 1)
)

)
